Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Associate Front-End Developer position with Springs Window Fashions. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web development, UI implementation, and API integration, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade user-facing features that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I developed UI components for an Identity & Access Management platform using React, Spring Boot, and AWS, implementing responsive layouts, cross-browser compatibility, and accessibility standards to support thousands of users across 30+ applications. This hands-on experience translating design requirements into functional, accessible web interfaces has prepared me to translate UI/UX wireframes into production-ready code and contribute meaningfully to building responsive layouts optimized for various devices and browsers. At Sperse, I built generative code solutions for developers — including API-aware templates, SDK patterns, and code-generation workflows — to accelerate API integration with platform endpoints and improve implementation correctness. I also developed user-facing features that translate natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints, implementing robust input validation and error handling. Additionally, I optimized routing and concurrency to maximize performance, reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and lowering API costs by 50% through targeted load time optimization strategies — directly mirroring the performance optimization and website maintenance responsibilities central to this role. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to the team's core front-end development responsibilities and drive impact within an agile engineering team.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in technical communication and collaborative problem-solving — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion to generate industry-standard fashion designs, leveraging CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster for model training and fine-tuning. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph, for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the collaboration and communication skills needed to work closely with designers and backend developers to integrate APIs and data into UI components. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to Springs Window Fashions and its mission.

I have always been passionate about creating the Best Experience through product quality, innovation, and accountability, and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Springs Window Fashions' vision of Inspiring Spaces, Brilliantly Simple. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

